@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About ASP.NET MVC ImageUpload Demo";
}

<div class="panel-body" id="accordion" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
    <h3>Basic MS MVC 5 / EntityFramework 6 Proofs of Concept</h3>
    <p>A basic image uploading application with CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) example using ASP.Net, MVC 5, Entity Framework 6</p>
</div>

<div class="panel-group" id="accordion" role="tablist" arial-multiselectable="true">
    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="functionalityHeading">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
                <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#functionality" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="functionality">
                    Basic Functionality / Concepts
                </a>
            </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="functionality" class="panel-collapse collapse in" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="functionalityHeading">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <ul>
                    <li>HTML Version</li>
                    <li>Basic CRUD</li>
                    <li>Bootstrap Styling</li>
                    <li>jQuery Framework</li>
                    <li>Built with Visual Studio 2013 Community</li>
                    <li>IIS 8 Express</li>
                    <li>Sql Express LocalDB</li>
                    <li>ASP.Net</li>
                    <li>EntityFramework 6</li>
                    <li>MS MVC 5</li>
                    <li>Razor Layouts</li>
                    <li>Razor HTML Pages</li>
                    <li>Model Column Annotations</li>
                    <li>Customized Controllers</li>
                    <li>Custom Data Seeding</li>
                    <li>ViewModel usages</li>
                    <li>Custom Helper Classes for Image Tag rendering</li>
                    <li>Custom ModelBinder classes</li>
                    <li>Custom Model Attributes</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <p>
                    This small app was developed to test out MS MVC's file uploading capabilities and as a proof of
                    concept for being able to do server-side image resizing (e.g., thumbnail generation) as an image
                    was uploaded.  The inspiration for this comes from the Ruby on Rails world - specifically a GEM
                    called PaperClip.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The bulk of the code in this project was generated by the various Visual Studio 2013 Wizards as
                    well as a couple of articles found via Google (why reinvent the wheel!)  There were 2 main articles
                    used:
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5013824/paperclip-for-asp-net-mvc">PaperClip for ASP.NET MVC</a></li>
                        <li><a href="http://www.c-sharpcorner.com/Blogs/8622/Asp-Net-mvc-imagefor-htmlhelper.aspx">Image Tag Helper for ASP.NET MVC</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <p>This app is NOT production-quality.  The code was developed for proof-of-concept only.  Feel free to download, cut it up, use parts 
                of it in any way desired.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
